caption: In a city full of takes on "premium" southern food, Phat Sammy's blazes their own path. You'll have to follow their Instagram to get a better picture of what they offer. I find myself going here more than any other joint because of their offerings. The chef nails it every time. If you want something different, or want culinary paradise, go here. I've been to restaurants where I may like the food but would visit once a year. Here? Once a month bare minimum.
How is this place so good?  I eat here everytime I'm in town and have been impressed by everything I've tried.
The drinks are great and the food is better.  Well done thank you.
Amazing
Unique food, unique drinks. All great!
They were out of Moco Loco at 6:30pm!

Definitely my favorite place to eat downtown. The food is always on point. Always something new and always something good. Their staples are just as great though.  I love their cocktails too. If you want something interesting, go on Wu Tang Wednesdays. They always make a specialty cocktail and it's always good. These are experienced bartenders. They know what's up, just like the food staff.  I wish I was rich where I could eat here every night.
Wutang Wednesday's are the best. They come up with some creative and delicious cocktails

We had a fantastic experience here! Service was super friendly and fast. We reserved a table for 2 at 7PM, got there early to have a drink and they said they could seat us immediately. We shared 2 apps and split a sandwich. We came hungry and it was still way too much for us. We will definitely go back to try some of their well known cocktails!
Phat Sammys is always delicious!

Phat Sammy's is an example of what restaurants are supposed to be. They're creative, fun, welcoming, and hard-working.  I had the special cray Bahn mi last night with pb&j wings. Ordered pickup and the order was ready 20 minutes later when I walked in the door after finding parking.  They're safe and sanitary with covid procedures. Their menu is full of great options. The staff is super friendly and prompt.  Nothing but great things to say about these guys.
Delicious and fun. Loved the fancy drinks, good food, and festive ambiance. 'Bout time we got a Tiki bar.

I had been following (ok stalking) them on Instagram for a while and was super excited when I finally had a chance to visit. We came with another adult couple and their children (three of them all under 5). We visited at lunch and there was only one other couple in the restaurant. We had cups for the kids so we only needed glasses for the adult. We started off with cocktails. The were all amazing. Mine was some sort of green tea infused vodka drink and I need it in my life again soon lol. Anyway, everyone enjoyed their drinks. Then we ordered 3 appetizers.  Only three of us ate and the other adult sat with the kids and read to them. All of the apps were unique and flavorful. The fries were great, the clams with some a bacon filled broth were also delicious, and the general tso wings were outstanding. The waitress even played with the youngest kid when he went exploring in the empty restaurant. Then came time for the bill. They added gratuity for a large group!! How? Why? You literally provided service for three adults for the whole dining experience. One adult ordered one cocktail and moved away from the table to play with the kids. This ruined my whole dining experience. They were basically empty and I guess adding gratuity was supposed to make up for a slow business day. Not cool at all. I’m giving three stars for the food and drink because yes they were great. Taking off two stars because you would have received a 20% tip regardless because the service was great. But including gratuity when you only serviced four people....not cool.

We had fantastic service, drinks and food. We ordered the General Tso’s wings, the BBQ pork belly, the chips and dip and the crabfat fried rice.  The sauces on both the wings and the pork belle were so rich and full of flavor and the wings and pork belly were cooked perfectly. The pork rinds on the chips and dip were so light and crispy. Our only complaint was the dips for the rinds was kinda bland and we didn’t feel it had much flavor, could have been partly due to the sauces for the wings and pork belly being so rich and flavorful.  The rice was a pleasant surprise and one we will definitely order again.  It had such a wonderful seafood flavor and was cooked perfectly.  Overall an amazing experience and one we plan to repeat soon!!

The atmosphere was super chill. They played great tunes. Customer service was on top of it. We shared the buns, phat fries and pork belly. The pork belly was melt in your mouth delicious. The spicy squid was indeed spicy! Whoo! Pairing it with the phat fries was the perfect way to go as the cheese and gravy on the fries calmed the spice down. I wish the phat fries had one more egg but they were delicious! The fries has good flavor on their own. Well seasoned. The gravy was flavorful. Everything came out at the right temperature and was the perfect sharing size.

Phat Sammy's is the literal best...I can't form my emotions into words. Also Shannon is the coolest and Jeremy is so great. Phat Sammy's is where I go for mental , physical healing Love all day to the tiki. Every bite is new
Great food and wonderful service. I will for sure be going back and will be recommending it to others.
Phat Sammy's is an awesome spot for super flavorful exciting food and the best cocktails in town. The folks who work there are always super friendly and the music is always 🔥. Would highly recommend.
Really nice place, good food, excellent cocktail.

Super expensive for the area.  If you cut all the prices in half, this place would be a decent value.  Weird plates and spoons and jugs to hold their "specialty drinks".  Food was ok.  Large servings.
Excellent service and food. Love the funky flare
Amazing food!

Atmosphere was interesting, we were told to go here by a friend and were massively disappointed.  Drinks are expensive, but the food was a weird mock up of what people think asian fusion is.  The "Phat fries" were smothering in gravy that blocked the flavor of any other elements and it becomes a wet mess of potatoes with no standout texture or flavors.  Anyone could know the taste of instant curry packets from any asian supermarket with one bite of the curry from here.  The katsu pork sandwich would've been fine had there not been a pile horseradish inside it which blocked any other flavors from actually making the sandwich enjoyable.  We won't be coming back and I encourage anyone to read the menu throughly before considering eating here because what might sound interesting could be a total disaster of elements that do not meld well on a plate.
Very unusual menu excellent server food was phenomenal. Really enjoyed our experience there

This place has a fun vibe and service was excellent. Trying to explain how the flavor combinations of the food works here won't do it justice. Try it - I think you'll like what all they have to offer.
A meal from here resulted in more heart burn and gas than from Bandito Burrito
Love this place! Spam fried rice is my favorite dish from here.
Excellent food!

They are easy to miss with the construction covering up the entrance on the street. Cool eclectic kind of place. Down the stairs. The menu is what convinced me to go. "Chips and Dip" nothing even close to what your thinking, smoked pork rinds, thai chili style marinara made with pork with a shallot cream cheese, Cilantro... delicious! You have got to read the menu. Octo-noms tender Octopus...Kimchi pizza, ask for a side of Sriracha! Tired of the same old same? But still just enough this side of the South to reel you in...Phat Fries, just think of an Asian dish (I am thinking Korean) fused with Poutine. Don't know what poutine is? Ya gotta Google it.  -- Read the menu, plan your visit, and we haven't even discussed the drinks yet. I hope it survives COVID and CONSTRUCTION downtown.
Foods so good and Amber's the best.

Fantastic food. Fresh ingredients and very generous portion sizes. The chips and dip is such a unique dish and is so delicious. The battleship curry had hearty chunks of chicken and veggies and tasted great.
Great everything!

This place slaps. We had the pork katsu sando, fried oyster buns, lamb chee sandwich, and phat fries. I haven't seen pork floss anywhere in HSV restaurants other than my mom's pantry - so kudos for the sick menu!

Great classic foods with an Asian flare.  Lots of ingredients that would only be available at a specialty grocery store, really impressed at the Chef's creativity and combinations.  Look for the pineapple to enter.
Very unique atmosphere and food and drink selection

This place earned five stars within five seconds of walking in, for two reasons: they were playing Biggie and the place just looked so cool. But really, the drinks were delicious and service super friendly. I’ve got to try the food next time because it smelled delicious, but was unfortunately only there for the drinks at the time. EDIT: went a second time and ordered food, and it was indeed delicious. The team here puts so much attention into each drink and dish, it’s astounding the amount they can do with the amount of space they have to do it. This place is an absolute must-try in Huntsville.

Food was awesome and service was absolutely amazing! The restaurant is so unique and cool, I can't recommend Phat Sammy's more so please go check it out for yourself! Make sure and try one of their signature drinks while you're there, delicious! I know I'll be visiting again soon! *They're being safe and make you feel comfortable during these rough times

Been here a few times and would give them an easy 5.1 stars every time, but when my wife and I went in on Election Day to celebrate our voting and await the conclusion, we came in, got our drinks as usual and then ordered our food, all was timely and pleasant as always, butttt then after we finished our food and single drink each(regular medium sized adult beverage) we didn’t hear another word from the bartender for another half hour to 45 minutes. By that time we were rather frustrated and when he asked ‘Hey, ready for a second drink?’ After we had been there for an hour+, we thanked him and decided for our check and to leave. It’s an odd thing in my opinion to have such a pleasant experience just to be filled by neglectful service timing. We even were sitting at the bar, so never more then a handful of feet from our tender, an you can’t just take a glance to check in on us? Regardless we will be back, I’ll chalk it up to an ‘off day’ for the guy.

Unbelievable good experience, great food, great staff, very clean, drinks are amazing, a safe place to eat, you might call ahead on the weekends to make a reservation, small place but well ventilated, large experience every time! Thank you Phat Sammy's for the excellent dining and for the care that you provide safety for your customers and staff! This is the only place I have gone to and felt safe at during the pandemic. Phat Sammy's rocks!
It's a super cool place to eat and drink!

Great local restaurant in downtown Huntsville. What a unique menu. Everything from burgers to bowls but with unique twist. I had the chili dog and it came with tofu chili. They also have a expansive drink menu. Fun drinks that are very creative as well.  It's a small venue with a fun atmosphere.
Great selection of Rums and liquors. The menu is simple but well cooked. Special of the day is worth checking. If you splurge with drinks your tab might reflect it.
Awesome atmosphere, conscientious of Covid, very very tasty food, unique drinks, and awesome weekly specials!
The food is amazing and the staff is awesome!

Yeah, try this place. GREAT drinks and fun atmosohere! I’ve been here twice now and Connor helped me both times. Super friendly, great recommendations, and attentive. Drinks are among the best in Alabama. Creative, very tasty, and not overstated.  Want a great classic old fashion?  Looking for something creative and new? Either way this is your place. Tonight they’re offering coconut and candied bacon old fashions and they’re spot on! And yes, I ate half my bacon before the picture.
Connor was a great server and helped us to decide what to order.
Amazing food, incredible drinks, great service! I will go back
The chef is a mad scientist who comes up with incredibly unique and delicious combinations. Try the kmac burger (possibly the best in town) or the lamb and chee.
Great experience, great food. Battleship curry was great comfort food

Tiki has finally come to Huntsville! And unlike a lot of other tiki bars, the food is just as amazing as the drinks. The food and drink menus are creative and there's always new food and drink specials. You have to check it out.

Very nice atmosphere and great bar team. Drinks are unique and taste great. However, all of their drinks are pretty overpriced in my opinion. I wouldn't come here unless you're willing to spend $40 for two drinks. For those with deep pockets, this is a great choice. However, if you're always looking at the prices and trying to save a buck, stay away.

This place is amazing!  The food is authentic from around the world.  I had the general tso wings and they may have been the best wings I have ever had.  The atmosphere is very islandy and the staff is great!  We will be back for sure.  Looking forward to one of the theme nights.  This place is a hidden gem for sure.
Love this place! Great service and wonderful atmosphere

Not worth the price. This is not my first choice of food type but it was not very flavorful. We got the chicken balls, general tso wings and pork katsu sandwich. The wings were the best of the meal and weren't bad but the overall food did not make us want to return. They do have an extensive drink menu!
Super Cool place with Super Cool Bartenders!! Epic ambiance!! Will definitely be back a ton!!!!
Great food, drinks, and atmosphere.

What a wonderful place to get away from it all. The food is good and the bar is outstanding. The signature and classic tiki cocktails are wonderful, but whether or not tiki is your thing, the bar staff are certain to make you something you enjoy. Whether you’re looking for a date night or a night with friends in Huntsville, Phat Sammy’s should be your first thought. It is mine!
Great first experience.  Great unique food, good drinks and atmosphere
Great Service, Great Food, Perfect Cocktails💫
Excellent food. Great choices for all kinds of dietary needs. Looking forward to relaxing there often after Covid is done!
Amazing place, great food and great vibes!

Fun Hawaiian, island drink bar.  This place has a festive feel, great food, and great drinks.  Their cocktails are island themed, and with with a neat presentation.  The food is also pretty tasty, and includes several creative dishes.  This place isn't too expensive, and doesn't take itself too seriously (although they kind of do).  Would certainly go again.

Certainly I must start by saying that I love this place. I have been many times. Tonight I am attending their Christmas in July festivities. Green Bean Casserole Wontons? Amazing. Sake-coladas? We kept ordering them! But then it gets to the Buddha's Delight sandwich.  The first time we ate here right after they opened we got the Buddha's Delight and it was amazing, delicious, warm, great. Today, our party got two of them between the four of us. To say it was gross is an understatement, and we are fairly sure it wasn't even tempeh this time. Unfortunately it was a bad night for those sandwiches as everything else was delicious.  Great restaurant and I hate not giving them 5 stars, but yall have a problem with the Buddha's Delight sandwich that is in desperate need of fixing.

Super cool servers. The atmosphere is just fun, funky and a bit tropical. Love how you feel like you're getting in somewhere on the down low but it turns out, it's a super cool place. Tasty drinks too
Secret Hawaiian getaway in the middle of town. Great food and great atmosphere.
Best Tiki drinks in town
Great atmosphere and unique dining options. The Smokey B was great!
Great addition to downtown Huntsville! The atmosphere was so much fun, the cocktails we're delish, and the food was GOOD!
Excellent drinks. Superb food. Get it.

Amazing concept that truly delivers the cool experience. We have been several times and are always happy. The drinks are strong, and who — going into an underground tiki bar — wouldn’t want that?! Phat fries are my go to every time. Well managed, immaculately clean while staying dedicated to their theme. Wish I could leave more than 5 stars.
Outstanding food! Great service, COVID compliant, fun place! Downtown TO-GO spot.

Really tasty drink adventures! Wish I could have tried them all. Will be back! Cool atmosphere. Also super yummy menu. Got the Phat Fries. Great location across from the parking garage. Bartenders were welcoming and knowledgeable. Excellent service!
Absolutely banging

Great atmosphere, kind waitstaff, hit-and-miss food.  My wife and I came to Phat Sammy's courtesy the perfect, five star review. Unfortunately, it seems as though we didn't get the same experience others have had.  First, though, let's parse out the good. Our server was an absolute treat, with a bubbly personality and an eagerness to make our experience a pleasant one. The atmosphere? The atmosphere was amazing! From the mural on the wall, to the seating and music, this was a really cool scene, with a lot of zest and excitement to it.  Unfortunately, though, there's a negative side to this story. This starts with the drinks. The cocktails were hit and miss. My wife's Punch was amazing, meanwhile my rum cocktail tasted like somebody filled the glass halfway with bottom shelf rum and made the grapefruit soda an afterthought. Don't get me wrong, if you're a fan of strong cocktails, this would probably be a win for you, but it was not the stuff of the nice, smooth rum cocktail I was expecting.  The food? Well, we started off with the Steamed Bun appetizer, and I can say, this was honestly delicious. Mind you, I say that as somebody who generally does not enjoy oysters, these were great. That's where the wow factor honestly ended, though.  My wife had the "Pineapple Goes on All Things" bowl and, as she told me, it was "Alright". It wasn't terrible, but it was not something to write home about, nor justify the price tag. Meanwhile, I had the K-Mac burger and fries.  My experience with the K-Mac started out with a mistake, when I was brought a rice dish instead of my fries. No big deal, of course, as this is easily rectified. However, the man who delivered our food shortly after realized the mistake and returned to the table. Rather than letting me know that they'd bring out my fries, he promptly reached over me and onto my plate to remove the bowl of rice and later return with my fries. Now, of course, I'm not one to be hung up on something I didn't order being taken away from my table, but reaching over and onto my plate just is not proper etiquette.  I'd realized we were running out of water at my table and figured, since he was there, I would ask that we had another bottle brought out. I was promptly informed that I would have to ask my waitress for that, and he hustled off. Again, questionable professionalism, as he could have just as easily acknowledged the request and let our server know.  Shortly after, our fries were brought out and we got our water refills. Ready to eat, I dug into my K-Mac and fries. The K-Mac itself left much to be desired, and struck me more as a gimmick burger than a well thought out recipe. The sauce was great, but the kimchi just did not vibe well with the patties, the carrots were a strange addition, as well. It's not that it was terrible, it just wasn't very good.  To summarize? Great atmosphere, friendly waitstaff, gimmicky food and less than pleasant/professional kitchen staff. Certainly not worth the nearly $70 tab.
Roses are red Violets are blue I like phat sammy’s You should too. 😘
I love the Phat Fries
Funky vibes and funky food. Unique to HSV. Creative local crew working on standards as well as weekly specials. Come with an open mind and a sense of adventure.
Phat Sammy’s has amazing food, cocktails, and atmosphere. The perfect place to meet a friend for drinks.
Phat Sammy's offers unique entrees and fun cocktails!

Had a chance to order take-out from Phat Sammy's today and wasn't disappointed! I ordered the Kimchi Pizza and Katsu Sando with Phat fries. Both were delicious! I can't wait to order more items off their menu in the future.
Phenomenal Korean Fried Chicken and delicious home made fries and sauces. Intriguing appetizers that are unusual and very welcome in this area.

We had phat fries and Brussels sprouts and it was absolutely amazing, it was such a wonderful menu and presentation with the dish.  Their drink selection is wide open and unique.  We are coming back again tonight.  Definitely addicted to the phat fries.  On top of just the food, the employees have all been upbeat and genuinely happy to be there.  Our bartender, Amber has such an amazing attitude and is just one of those people that makes you happy to be there and she purely makes Phat Sammys such a warm and wonderful place.  Thank you guys for bringing such wonderful food and service to us in Huntsville. We will always be patrons.
Best food in Huntsville. Very unique atmosphere!
Incredible food that never disappoints! I highly recommend the Beyond Bangkok burger.
Delicious food,  great atmosphere and awesome service!  Definitely a must try!
Ordered two dishes to-go and both were SO good. Generous portion sizes, interesting spices that made for awesome flavors, and just the right amount of spiciness! We’ll totally be back for more.
Gorgeous space, fantastic service and literally some of the BEST food in Huntsville.
Excellent new bar/restaurant in the heart of downtown!
Wonderful!!! I had the Phat Fries and they were amazing!!!!!! Definitely a meal in itself even though it’s an appetizer. I can’t wait to go back when the inside is open!
This place so unique and awesome. The food was DELICIOUS and our server was fantastic.
Food was delicious. Atmosphere is great!

When you step into this place, you dont feel like its Huntsville. One of a kind drinks, food, service and atmosphere. Happy to see a true HSV original. I believe they will set the standard for many businesses to come that will ultimately shape the future of downtown Huntsville. If this is the beginning,  I cant wait to watch you guys grow.
Great atmosphere! Beautiful decor! And the food is amazing. You will definitely feel like you’re in a different city.

Super atmospheric tiki bar with great music pumping, insanely good food coming out of the kitchen, cocktails that you won't get anywhere else in Huntsville. One of the best additions to downtown in years!
